1
00:01:36,990 --> 00:01:40,150
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,090
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:44,539
I should be like him.

4
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:46,180
I don't care anymore.

5
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:47,500
Do as you please.

6
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:50,920
I told Duojie earlier

7
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,590
not to let you into the mountains

8
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,789
and made you unhappy.

9
00:01:56,979 --> 00:01:58,310
I was being meddlesome.

10
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:02,700
Mom.

11
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:06,380
What are you talking about?

12
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:08,620
Look.

13
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:10,250
I said you'd freeze.

14
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,430
You didn't listen.

15
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,500
You never listen to me.

16
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,300
Hurry inside.

17
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:13,990
Hurry.

18
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:15,750
Go near to the stove.

19
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,470
Are there any more towels?

20
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:16,970
Yes.

21
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:39,740
Your brother

22
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:41,150
named the little foal

23
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:42,070
Jiongxi.

24
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:44,790
Have you two discuss about it?

25
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,360
What do you want to name it?

26
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:48,760
Let's just call it Jiongxi.

27
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,630
He thought the name I picked

28
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:51,520
was too girly.

29
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,610
When are you going back to school?

30
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:57,800
Tomorrow, I guess.

31
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:01,320
Where are you going for your internship?

32
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,410
I want to go to Bolamula

33
00:03:02,410 --> 00:03:03,650
with my professor.

34
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,560
Once you graduate,

35
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:08,740
you probably

36
00:03:08,740 --> 00:03:09,800
won't return here.

37
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:11,360
The most beautiful girl

38
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,020
on the grasslands is leaving.

39
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:13,990
I wonder

40
00:03:14,010 --> 00:03:15,010
how many young men

41
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:16,230
will be heartbroken.

42
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,200
The most heartbroken one

43
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:19,920
is of course

44
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,380
that old man named Duojie.

45
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:36,280
Dolma.

46
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:40,730
Dolma.

47
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:43,860
Dolma.

48
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,300
Dolma.

49
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,360
Dolma.

50
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:05,780
Duojie.

51
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,500
County Mayor Duo,

52
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,150
you;ve just recovered.

53
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,410
You can't go anywhere.

54
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,000
At least wait for the checkup to be done.

55
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,590
I don't want to do any checkups.

56
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:12,610
I want to go home now.

57
00:04:12,610 --> 00:04:13,610
Finish the checkup,

58
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:14,430
and I'll take you home, okay?

59
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,020
Let go of me.

60
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:15,420
You...

61
00:05:32,090 --> 00:05:33,090
County Mayor Lin.

62
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,159
Reporter Shao.

63
00:05:37,290 --> 00:05:38,790
Are you leaving?

64
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:40,540
There are no more buses today.

65
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,770
I'll arrange a driver for you.

66
00:05:41,770 --> 00:05:42,370
No, no, no.

67
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:43,070
County Mayor Lin,

68
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:43,670
I came here

69
00:05:43,690 --> 00:05:44,930
to report to you.

70
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:46,250
I've decided

71
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,220
to stay with the Mountain Patrol.

72
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,270
I've already reported to the leaders

73
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,330
at my press office.

74
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:53,920
They agreed

75
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:54,720
to extend my creative leave

76
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,720
by another month.

77
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,380
And I proposed that

78
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:57,300
from now on,

79
00:05:58,130 --> 00:05:59,070
my personal safety

80
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,410
is my own responsibility.

81
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:02,210
The county won't be held liable.

82
00:06:02,770 --> 00:06:03,520
Then...

83
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:05,000
did your boss agree to it?

84
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,430
He didn't say no.

85
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:08,310
Nonsense.

86
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:09,420
County Mayor Lin,

87
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,190
come with me.

88
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,130
I am not your boss.

89
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:28,630
Technically,

90
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,760
I can't control you.

91
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,330
But,

92
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:32,409
as the County Mayor of Mazhi County,

93
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:33,360
there are a few things

94
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,500
I must remind you of.

95
00:06:37,659 --> 00:06:39,320
Don't need to write this down.

96
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:40,670
Right now,

97
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,450
it is a critical stage
for attracting investment.

98
00:06:42,450 --> 00:06:44,090
Two mining companies

99
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,890
are already preparing for pilot work.

100
00:06:45,890 --> 00:06:46,450
Even if

101
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,630
poaching and illegal mining in Bolamula

102
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,180
are facts,

103
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,450
if there are too many reports on them,

104
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:51,770
will it be good for the county's image

105
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:53,060
or helpful in boosting

106
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,500
the investor confidence?

107
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:55,740
If they get cold feet,

108
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:57,130
I have to humble myself

109
00:06:57,130 --> 00:06:58,600
and beg them to come back.

110
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:02,190
Shao, I'll say it again.

111
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:04,490
It's fine if you don't help me,

112
00:07:04,890 --> 00:07:05,530
But can you

113
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,960
not cause trouble for me?

114
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:10,980
County Mayor Lin,

115
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:13,010
news coverage

116
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:13,450
is never

117
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:14,500
to help someone

118
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,410
nor cause trouble to someone,

119
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:17,930
but to objectively and accurately

120
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:19,190
reflect social realities,

121
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:20,810
and to promote social progress

122
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:23,010
and satisfy the public's right to know.

123
00:07:23,010 --> 00:07:23,950
The story of the Mountain Patrol

124
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:24,700
moved me.

125
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,220
I have the motivation
and the responsibility

126
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:27,510
to finish this report.

127
00:07:27,930 --> 00:07:29,060
As for your concerns,

128
00:07:29,060 --> 00:07:30,510
I understand them very well.

129
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:31,600
The economic and livelihood issues

130
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,980
faced by the Mazhi County,

131
00:07:32,980 --> 00:07:33,750
I will truthfully

132
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:34,690
include them in the report.

133
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:35,890
Please rest assured.

134
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:40,820
Goodbye, County Mayor Lin.

135
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:43,370
Reporter Shao.

136
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:45,440
County Mayor Lin.

137
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,570
Why didn't you go in?

138
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,890
Did you see Danzhou?

139
00:07:51,890 --> 00:07:52,570
No.

140
00:07:52,650 --> 00:07:54,040
I haven't seen him for days.

141
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:54,700
Go find him.

142
00:07:54,930 --> 00:07:55,360
Tell him to come

143
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,820
to my office immediately.

144
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,310
[Mazhi County Public Security Bureau]

145
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,380
I've read the report

146
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:00,310
on this operation.

147
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,900
I'll assign you a new task now.

148
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:02,630
Come with me.

149
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,040
Wang.

150
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:06,370
Bai is here.

151
00:08:06,990 --> 00:08:08,050
Let me introduce.

152
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:10,110
You can just call her Ms. Wang.

153
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,570
You must know her, right?

154
00:08:11,570 --> 00:08:12,370
Hello, Sister Wang.

155
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:13,420
We know each other.

156
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:13,940
Strictly speaking,

157
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:15,370
she should call me Auntie.

158
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:16,100
I handled all the paperwork

159
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,100
for her adoption.

160
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:17,690
Yes.

161
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:19,130
My mom mentions you often.

162
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:19,860
Auntie Wang.

163
00:08:19,890 --> 00:08:21,160
I don't want to be called that.

164
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,360
It makes me sound old.

165
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:23,130
Just call me Miss.

166
00:08:23,130 --> 00:08:24,360
Come here. This will be your desk.

167
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:26,010
Yes, just call her Miss. Come.

168
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:27,010
Just call me Miss.

169
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:29,160
Thank you, Ms. Wang.

170
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:30,980
Well...

171
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:32,490
From now on,

172
00:08:32,770 --> 00:08:34,150
just work here comfortably.

173
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,890
Ask if there's anything
you don't understand.

174
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,409
Ms. Wang knows the operations very well.

175
00:08:37,409 --> 00:08:38,799
Got it. Thanks, Chief.

176
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:39,940
Don't worry, Chief.

177
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:41,440
Young people learn fast.

178
00:08:41,530 --> 00:08:42,409
You go ahead and get busy.

179
00:08:42,409 --> 00:08:43,890
I'll brief Bai on the situation.

180
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,350
Okay, I'll leave it to you.

181
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:46,100
Sure.

182
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:46,890
Sit down.

183
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,740
Don't feel pressured.

184
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:52,820
The work here

185
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,480
is much easier than the Mountain Patrol's.

186
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,030
First, I'll teach you how
to set up a household registration.

187
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:56,500
This

188
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:57,750
is the most basic task.

189
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,210
Then there's
replacing the household registration.

190
00:08:59,210 --> 00:08:59,810
Some herdsmen

191
00:08:59,810 --> 00:09:00,770
don't take good care of their booklets

192
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:01,370
and lose them,

193
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:02,900
so they need replacements.

194
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,000
We went into the mountains

195
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,050
with Chief Shi and his men,

196
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:12,860
but we still didn't catch

197
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:13,630
that boss.

198
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:16,740
There are a dozen members

199
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:18,050
of the Criminal Investigation Division
and county militia

200
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:18,740
left in there

201
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:20,070
to continue searching.

202
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:21,530
We explained the way out

203
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,430
very clearly to them.

204
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,340
Don't worry,

205
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,900
there won't be any danger.

206
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:27,490
After all, they have

207
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,480
much more ammunition and supplies

208
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,580
than we do.

209
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,980
Also,

210
00:09:38,030 --> 00:09:39,760
Director Zhang still suggests

211
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:40,480
that you head to the city

212
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,870
for a checkup

213
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:43,010
in a few days.

214
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,270
After all, the facilities there

215
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:46,670
-is much better than here.
-Where is Bai Ju?

216
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:53,320
Why haven't I seen her?

217
00:10:00,650 --> 00:10:03,450
She went back to wor
at the Public Security Bureau.

218
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,940
Chief Shi Long said

219
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,510
he's going to transfer a male officer

220
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:07,370
to your team.

221
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:08,840
Yes.

222
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,450
Here are the candidates

223
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:15,310
recommended by the Public Security Bureau.

224
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:16,000
Take a look.

225
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,320
Did you agree to let her go?

226
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:36,430
You all agree to let her go,

227
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,010
didn't you?

228
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:42,630
Speak.

229
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:44,070
What are you doing?

230
00:10:44,230 --> 00:10:45,020
Bai herself

231
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,770
agreed to be transferred back.

232
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,130
Why are you yelling?

233
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:04,330
Talk properly.

234
00:11:19,070 --> 00:11:20,600
She made such a big mistake.

235
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,460
She should leave.

236
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,240
Han.

237
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:34,980
How long have you been in the mountains?

238
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:38,650
Over a year.

239
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,280
I was released in September

240
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:42,960
and joined you guys since then.

241
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,890
I mean,

242
00:11:46,010 --> 00:11:47,210
before you joined us.

243
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:57,310
Two and a half years.

244
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:01,350
How many sheep did you hunt?

245
00:12:01,830 --> 00:12:03,140
More than 500, I think.

246
00:12:06,570 --> 00:12:07,920
I was sentenced for 500.

247
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:14,870
Zhacuo.

248
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:17,160
Once on patrol,

249
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,370
we reached the entrance
of Mountain Fenghuo

250
00:12:19,370 --> 00:12:20,270
and we lost all the food.

251
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:21,200
What happened?

252
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:24,130
It was me.

253
00:12:24,460 --> 00:12:25,280
I used it

254
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,290
for Kora.

255
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:28,650
To find you,

256
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:29,790
we didn't even complete

257
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:30,920
the patrol mission.

258
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:32,590
I was wrong.

259
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,510
I already apologized.

260
00:12:36,910 --> 00:12:37,550
Sangba.

261
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,670
That time you went home,

262
00:12:40,450 --> 00:12:42,050
when your mom gave you the cow

263
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:43,980
and asked you to come back,

264
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:44,910
what did she say?

265
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,650
Mom said...

266
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,440
"If a pillar in the temple breaks,

267
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:51,480
one person alone can't fix it.

268
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:53,480
Everyone must offer support

269
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,290
to fix it.

270
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:57,740
If the Mountain Patrol lacks me,

271
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,800
this house will also collapse."

272
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:15,060
Today's...

273
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,120
Wait a moment, it's almost done.

274
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:32,770
How can I help you?

275
00:13:34,170 --> 00:13:34,960
Come with me.

276
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:45,360
I think it's still too early

277
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:47,620
for you to return to the Mountain Patrol.

278
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,030
Are you saying that

279
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,150
to yourself too?

280
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:52,350
What do you mean?

281
00:14:56,890 --> 00:14:57,770
I mean,

282
00:14:57,870 --> 00:15:00,200
you haven't learned how to fight back yet.

283
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:02,620
When we herdsmen fight,

284
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:04,480
we solve the problems ourselves.

285
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:08,080
When you wanted to go into the mountains
back then,

286
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,080
you argued with me,

287
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,480
and argued with your mom.

288
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,460
Wasn't that because you wanted

289
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:14,060
to control your own destiny?

290
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:15,940
Why is it that as soon as I'm down,

291
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:17,200
you stop fighting?

292
00:15:19,050 --> 00:15:20,030
I just

293
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,000
can't work with people

294
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,650
who don't approve of me.

295
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:25,960
No one can possibly

296
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,420
get everyone's approval.

297
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:30,100
So this is a problem

298
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:31,590
you need to learn to solve.

299
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:38,190
Everyone has things beyond their control.

300
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:39,390
Aren't you the same?

301
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:41,000
You clearly don't approve of

302
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,290
the development zone

303
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:44,010
but you can't stop it,

304
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:47,150
and you're still at odds with the county.

305
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:49,390
Yeah.

306
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,130
We all have to learn.

307
00:15:52,740 --> 00:15:53,600
Keep learning.

308
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:55,860
I thought

309
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,650
once I was down and couldn't get up,

310
00:15:57,650 --> 00:16:00,580
I wouldn't have to worry
about these things anymore.

311
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,380
But now that I'm up,

312
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:04,740
it's still our business.

313
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:08,760
There is an old Tibetan saying.

314
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:13,360
"If you don't finish the path
you must walk,

315
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:13,960
you'll never reach

316
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,360
the place you want to go."

317
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,210
While you were in the hospital,

318
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:25,910
the county held a meeting

319
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:27,710
to disband the Mountain Patrol.

320
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:29,150
I heard.

321
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:32,110
It was County Mayor Lin
who firmly disagreed

322
00:16:32,110 --> 00:16:32,960
and saved us.

323
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:34,360
I know.

324
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:36,870
I didn't expect him

325
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:37,800
to do that.

326
00:16:39,630 --> 00:16:40,290
It doesn't surprise me at all

327
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,550
that Lin would do that.

328
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:43,410
The two of us

329
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:44,240
have argued a lot

330
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,220
about work.

331
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:47,240
But we have never

332
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,100
held a grudge against each other.

333
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,650
Because our goals

334
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:53,150
are never for ourselves.

335
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:56,370
If there were more officials

336
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:57,670
like him,

337
00:16:58,700 --> 00:16:59,200
Mazhi County

338
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,130
would definitely develop better.

339
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:12,250
Bai.

340
00:17:12,569 --> 00:17:13,480
Captain.

341
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,339
The Captain is back.

342
00:17:15,339 --> 00:17:16,190
Bai is back.

343
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:29,720
Bai,

344
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:31,400
welcome back to the hardship.

345
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:38,670
♪ We gather here today ♪

346
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:45,590
♪ I hope we will never be apart ♪

347
00:17:45,710 --> 00:17:48,160
♪ People who love each other ♪

348
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,110
There's a bit left.

349
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:46,770
Who wants it?

350
00:18:46,770 --> 00:18:47,090
Captain.

351
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:47,680
I'm full.

352
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:49,260
You guys go ahead.

353
00:18:50,820 --> 00:18:51,550
Give me some.

354
00:18:54,290 --> 00:18:55,180
Bad news!

355
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,170
Bad news!

356
00:18:56,570 --> 00:18:57,370
What's wrong?

357
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,430
Is the wolf here?

358
00:18:58,590 --> 00:18:59,200
Chair...

359
00:18:59,550 --> 00:18:59,990
Chair... Chair...

360
00:18:59,990 --> 00:19:00,660
The Chairman is coming.

361
00:19:00,660 --> 00:19:01,790
Who?

362
00:19:02,030 --> 00:19:02,830
Who's coming?

363
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,280
The Chairman.

364
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:06,920
We have

365
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,740
a Chairman here?

366
00:19:12,780 --> 00:19:13,630
Let him come.

367
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:18,370
We have to come clean sooner or later.

368
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:36,880
Shao.

369
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:37,750
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

370
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:38,440
Welcome.

371
00:19:39,330 --> 00:19:40,530
What brings you here?

372
00:19:41,070 --> 00:19:41,680
Uncle Ding and the others

373
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,510
aren't used to driving on mountain roads,

374
00:19:42,510 --> 00:19:43,590
so I drove for them.

375
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:45,220
Is that so?

376
00:19:47,070 --> 00:19:47,930
Chairman Ding.

377
00:19:48,010 --> 00:19:48,710
Welcome.

378
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:50,820
I heard you were injured.

379
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:52,150
Is it serious?

380
00:19:52,570 --> 00:19:53,690
Thanks for your concern.

381
00:19:53,690 --> 00:19:54,890
I'm fully recovered.

382
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:56,030
That's good.

383
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,910
Heaven watches over good people.

384
00:19:57,910 --> 00:19:58,440
How is it?

385
00:19:59,050 --> 00:19:59,960
Let's go inside first.

386
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:00,330
Okay.

387
00:20:01,220 --> 00:20:02,220
Hello, Chairman Ding.

388
00:20:02,220 --> 00:20:03,820
Thank you for your hard work.

389
00:20:04,270 --> 00:20:04,850
Xi.

390
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:06,060
Hello.

391
00:20:06,090 --> 00:20:07,220
Thank you, everyone.

392
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:08,080
Let's go, Shao.

393
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:08,770
Chairman Ding.

394
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:09,310
Good work.

395
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:10,300
Good work, everyone.

396
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:10,820
Han,

397
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,290
bring my sister to the room first.

398
00:20:12,290 --> 00:20:12,620
Shao,

399
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:13,980
I'll go find you something good to eat.

400
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:14,550
No need.

401
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:17,250
Go sit up there.

402
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:19,970
Brothers.

403
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,200
Hello.

404
00:20:27,010 --> 00:20:28,240
Don't worry.

405
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,070
I won't forget

406
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:31,240
you hungry wolves.

407
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:37,870
There's plenty of everything.

408
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:38,610
Shao,

409
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:39,880
The dried beef from Mrs. Nima

410
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,330
is super delicious.

411
00:20:41,940 --> 00:20:42,480
Try it.

412
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:49,350
Shao?

413
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,760
What's wrong?

414
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,510
We're not staying here.

415
00:20:53,510 --> 00:20:54,510
Come home with me.

416
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,350
Shao.

417
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:56,500
Shao.

418
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:57,900
Why would I go home?

419
00:20:58,550 --> 00:20:59,290
Why are...

420
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,540
Why are you crying?

421
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:01,720
Didn't you tell me

422
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,240
that you were

423
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,700
doing fine here?

424
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,720
How is this fine?

425
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:07,750
How can anyone live here?

426
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:09,910
Shao.

427
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:10,540
Shao.

428
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:11,900
It's good enough.

429
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,240
This is even a private room.

430
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:14,970
Same treatment as the Captain.

431
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:16,420
I knew the Mountain Patrol

432
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:17,680
has tough conditions,

433
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:18,530
but I didn't expect it

434
00:21:18,530 --> 00:21:19,940
to be this bad.

435
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:21,980
Look...

436
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:24,310
Look at you.

437
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,320
You are a perfectly good

438
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,260
police academy graduate.

439
00:21:28,770 --> 00:21:29,180
How...

440
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:30,200
how can you stay here

441
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,550
and suffer like this?

442
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:32,610
I don't care.

443
00:21:32,610 --> 00:21:33,220
You're coming home with me.

444
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:34,480
-I’ll tell Mom
-Shao.

445
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,250
to not let you stay here anymore.

446
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:36,310
Shao, listen to me.

447
00:21:37,210 --> 00:21:37,860
Shao!

448
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:44,640
We're not staying here.

449
00:21:46,110 --> 00:21:46,980
Listen to me.

450
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:50,140
I like being here.

451
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:51,700
I don't like

452
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:54,250
working a desk job
at the Public Security Bureau.

453
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:54,960
Besides,

454
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:56,680
I'm not suffering here.

455
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:58,210
Your bank dormitory

456
00:21:58,330 --> 00:21:59,500
and duty rooms,

457
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:00,660
don't they all have hard beds too?

458
00:22:00,660 --> 00:22:01,660
It's all the same.

459
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:02,810
How is that the same?

460
00:22:02,830 --> 00:22:03,700
Look at this.

461
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:04,390
Just look.

462
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,640
This place is so drafty.

463
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:06,420
How is anyone supposed to live here?

464
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:08,110
It must be freezing at night.

465
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:09,850
Yes.

466
00:22:10,290 --> 00:22:11,790
The house is a bit old.

467
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,300
But look.

468
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:13,810
Shao.

469
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:14,890
Look.

470
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:16,310
Look how thick the walls are.

471
00:22:16,310 --> 00:22:16,830
When you sleep at night,

472
00:22:16,830 --> 00:22:17,510
it's not cold at all.

473
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:18,510
It's really warm.

474
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,550
Really.

475
00:22:24,130 --> 00:22:25,090
Don't cry.

476
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:27,140
It's fine.

477
00:22:27,170 --> 00:22:28,740
Stop crying.

478
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:30,350
You won't look pretty if you keep crying.

479
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:31,500
Don't give me that.

480
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:34,350
Shao.

481
00:22:36,610 --> 00:22:37,540
When you go back,

482
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,000
don't tell Mom anything.

483
00:22:39,740 --> 00:22:41,670
Or she won't be able to sleep again.

484
00:22:41,690 --> 00:22:42,470
Shao, sit.

485
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:44,230
Sit down.

486
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:48,530
Try this.

487
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,160
The beef jerky is delicious.

488
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:50,750
Really.

489
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:51,720
Try it.

490
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,980
Why are you crying again?

491
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:05,810
Shao,

492
00:23:07,140 --> 00:23:09,000
you and Chairman Ding's son

493
00:23:09,110 --> 00:23:10,500
are dating,

494
00:23:10,630 --> 00:23:11,300
aren't you?

495
00:23:16,810 --> 00:23:17,850
No.

496
00:23:22,220 --> 00:23:23,020
We're just...

497
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:24,970
platonic friends.

498
00:23:25,710 --> 00:23:26,160
Did you forget

499
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,250
what I do?

500
00:23:27,830 --> 00:23:29,240
I never forget a face.

501
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,450
He went to your bank to see you.

502
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:32,850
He's that...

503
00:23:32,850 --> 00:23:33,980
weirdo who doesn't feel the cold.

504
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,840
You... you're talking nonsense.

505
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:41,850
Well,

506
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,060
you can't tell Mom about this.

507
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:45,770
If you don't tell Mom about me,

508
00:23:46,420 --> 00:23:47,940
I won't tell her about you.

509
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:57,040
Pinky swear.

510
00:23:57,630 --> 00:23:58,360
Pinky swear.

511
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,230
But Shao,

512
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,250
if you date him,

513
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:11,410
and you two are so far apart,

514
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:14,190
it'll be a long-distance relationship.

515
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:18,340
Who knows about the future?

516
00:24:18,940 --> 00:24:20,350
No one can say for sure.

517
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:22,030
Just see how it goes.

518
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:23,900
Anyway, he won't be leaving

519
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:24,740
anytime soon.

520
00:24:25,350 --> 00:24:26,070
He has to stay here

521
00:24:26,070 --> 00:24:28,000
and exploit a mine with his father.

522
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:30,310
But Shao,

523
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:34,850
the mining might not happen.

524
00:24:38,850 --> 00:24:39,700
Why?

525
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:46,500
What...

526
00:24:46,910 --> 00:24:47,840
What do you mean?

527
00:24:48,850 --> 00:24:49,710
Chairman Ding.

528
00:24:50,980 --> 00:24:52,330
We are not doing
mineral exploration anymore.

529
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:53,660
Not exploring anymore?

530
00:24:53,990 --> 00:24:54,710
Yes.

531
00:24:55,090 --> 00:24:56,350
Are you lacking equipment,

532
00:24:56,350 --> 00:24:57,010
personnel,

533
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:57,980
or funds?

534
00:24:58,070 --> 00:24:59,310
Tell me what you need.

535
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,940
We are stopping
the mineral exploration completely.

536
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:04,750
We are not building
the Economic Development Zone either.

537
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:06,160
We are planning to establish

538
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:07,160
a nature reserve.

539
00:25:08,420 --> 00:25:09,400
A reserve?

540
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:13,930
What exactly are you protecting?

541
00:25:15,070 --> 00:25:18,110
Protect the snow-capped mountains,
lakes, and rivers.

542
00:25:18,110 --> 00:25:19,220
Protect every flower and blade of grass

543
00:25:19,220 --> 00:25:20,170
in Bolamula,

544
00:25:20,550 --> 00:25:21,530
as well as the wild animals

545
00:25:21,530 --> 00:25:22,400
living inside.

546
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:24,740
This means

547
00:25:25,350 --> 00:25:26,270
Bolamula

548
00:25:26,370 --> 00:25:28,100
will be completely closed off.

549
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:29,220
No business activities

550
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:29,960
are allowed.

551
00:25:30,610 --> 00:25:31,670
Are you playing me?

552
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:33,320
Do you know that

553
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,100
I've sunk my entire fortune

554
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:35,150
into this?

555
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,250
You keep changing your mind.

556
00:25:36,250 --> 00:25:38,090
You just want to screw me over, don't you?

557
00:25:38,090 --> 00:25:40,270
I didn't expect to get rich off you,

558
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,160
but there's no reason

559
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,690
to make me lose everything.

560
00:25:49,650 --> 00:25:51,580
How are you going to compensate me?

561
00:25:51,770 --> 00:25:52,310
Tell me.

562
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:57,460
Chairman Ding.

563
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,150
We can never repay your kindness

564
00:26:00,150 --> 00:26:01,670
in this lifetime.

565
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:05,680
You paid the rent

566
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,640
for this house.

567
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,400
You had someone

568
00:26:09,450 --> 00:26:11,070
to install the telephone line.

569
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:12,200
It's fair to say that

570
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,140
without you,

571
00:26:13,590 --> 00:26:15,520
there would be no Mountain Patrol.

572
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:17,420
You are like a father

573
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:17,920
to the Mountain Patrol.

574
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,140
Don't give me that.

575
00:26:20,070 --> 00:26:20,930
Let me tell you.

576
00:26:22,190 --> 00:26:23,580
I'm not that noble.

577
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,160
Don't forget

578
00:26:26,550 --> 00:26:27,750
what you promised me.

579
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,650
I lost 1.5 million.

580
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,680
You will compensate me for all of it.

581
00:26:34,090 --> 00:26:35,550
I can't pay this money back

582
00:26:35,610 --> 00:26:37,110
anytime soon.

583
00:26:38,030 --> 00:26:39,030
But I acknowledge

584
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,030
this debt.

585
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:42,350
My family's pasture

586
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:44,410
produces some Cordyceps every year.

587
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:45,920
I'll give it all to you.

588
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:47,130
Keep track of

589
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,360
how much it sells for.

590
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,000
I think in ten

591
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:51,390
or twenty years,

592
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,280
I'll eventually pay it off.

593
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,130
You've really screwed me over.

594
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:12,280
I'm sorry.

595
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,050
This is my fate.

596
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:27,440
It was destined

597
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:30,430
that I wouldn't find any minerals.

598
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:33,570
In business,

599
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:37,080
you win some, you lose some.

600
00:27:38,550 --> 00:27:39,250
This time,

601
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:41,980
I lost completely.

602
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:44,570
But there's no reason

603
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,720
for you

604
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,210
to take the fall for me.

605
00:27:47,430 --> 00:27:48,570
That's not how we Cantonese

606
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:49,290
do business.

607
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:50,110
Listen to me.

608
00:27:56,730 --> 00:27:58,390
If your family has Cordyceps,

609
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:00,640
give me some.

610
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:03,550
Consider it a proof that

611
00:28:04,070 --> 00:28:05,800
I didn't come here for nothing.

612
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:07,640
As for the future,

613
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:09,680
forget it.

614
00:28:09,850 --> 00:28:11,510
Just pretend I was never here.

615
00:28:11,850 --> 00:28:12,480
No, no, no.

616
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,090
Chairman Ding,

617
00:28:15,010 --> 00:28:15,610
I will definitely

618
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:16,700
repay this debt.

619
00:28:19,650 --> 00:28:21,380
How are you going to pay me back?

620
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,050
Take a look.

621
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,580
Just look at it.

622
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:26,460
Look how poor you are.

623
00:28:26,660 --> 00:28:28,390
Do you want me to raid your home?

624
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:32,410
What do you take me for?

625
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,330
Take it.

626
00:28:42,530 --> 00:28:43,390
I can't take it.

627
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:45,380
It's not for you.

628
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:48,880
It's for the Reserve.

629
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,130
Just consider it

630
00:28:52,810 --> 00:28:54,070
my small contribution

631
00:28:55,140 --> 00:28:56,270
to the Reserve.

632
00:28:58,220 --> 00:28:59,660
Building some good karma

633
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:02,510
for my future generations.

634
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:34,850
Tashi.

635
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:36,230
Hurry up and eat.

636
00:29:36,230 --> 00:29:37,690
You'll be late for school.

637
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,400
Okay.

638
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:49,220
Take the tsampa.

639
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:50,730
Eat it on the way.

640
00:29:53,070 --> 00:29:54,070
I'm off to school.

641
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:13,990
The Chairman agreed.

642
00:30:14,790 --> 00:30:15,500
He agreed.

643
00:30:15,850 --> 00:30:17,510
I'll bring it to him right now.

644
00:30:18,830 --> 00:30:19,960
I saved a little bit

645
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:21,290
to nourish your body.

646
00:30:26,010 --> 00:30:26,720
I'm fine.

647
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:28,990
You haven't been well lately.

648
00:30:28,990 --> 00:30:29,920
Keep it for yourself.

649
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:30,770
I don't want it.

650
00:30:30,770 --> 00:30:31,340
Keep it.

651
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:10,370
Why haven't you left for school?

652
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:11,590
Mom said

653
00:31:11,700 --> 00:31:12,940
after selling the Cordyceps,

654
00:31:12,940 --> 00:31:14,470
she'd buy me a game console.

655
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,530
Now the Cordyceps are gone.

656
00:31:16,830 --> 00:31:18,290
And so is the game console.

657
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:23,030
I took the Cordyceps

658
00:31:23,270 --> 00:31:24,440
for work matters.

659
00:31:25,350 --> 00:31:25,770
As for the game console,

660
00:31:25,770 --> 00:31:27,170
I'll buy it for you later.

661
00:31:27,750 --> 00:31:28,770
Grandma said

662
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,220
those who break their promises

663
00:31:30,220 --> 00:31:31,480
will have light souls.

664
00:31:31,830 --> 00:31:32,670
Even the lake water

665
00:31:32,670 --> 00:31:34,270
won't reflect their shadow.

666
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,350
So, the one who lost their shadow,

667
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:36,440
is it you or Mom?

668
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:17,510
[Mazhi County People's Hospital]

669
00:32:19,460 --> 00:32:20,390
Director Zhang.

670
00:32:21,030 --> 00:32:21,880
Secretary Li.

671
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:22,580
I'm so sorry

672
00:32:22,580 --> 00:32:23,440
for being late.

673
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,770
Mr. Wang from the cafeteria

674
00:32:25,770 --> 00:32:27,170
suddenly called in sick.

675
00:32:27,710 --> 00:32:28,900
I just finished cooking.

676
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:29,810
Have a seat.

677
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:30,450
Sit down.

678
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:32,180
Okay.

679
00:32:32,820 --> 00:32:34,420
So the Union Chairman

680
00:32:35,070 --> 00:32:36,120
has become a chef?

681
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:37,720
Now it's

682
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:39,350
Chairman Gewang,

683
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:41,140
Doctor Gewang,

684
00:32:41,420 --> 00:32:42,750
and Accountant Gewang.

685
00:32:42,850 --> 00:32:44,040
I don't even know

686
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:45,790
what I'm supposed to do anymore.

687
00:32:45,790 --> 00:32:46,470
We are all

688
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:47,700
bricks of the revolution.

689
00:32:47,700 --> 00:32:49,100
We go where we're needed.

690
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:52,970
Well, it's time to do
some heavy lifting now.

691
00:32:53,270 --> 00:32:54,130
Didn't the city

692
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:55,360
just give us

693
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:56,800
50,000 yuan

694
00:32:56,930 --> 00:32:58,590
to renovate the shower rooms?

695
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,380
I've already contacted

696
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:01,660
the construction team.

697
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:03,110
The foreman is from my hometown.

698
00:33:03,110 --> 00:33:04,380
He agreed to lower the price

699
00:33:04,380 --> 00:33:05,960
and take on the project.

700
00:33:06,850 --> 00:33:08,180
Regarding this matter,

701
00:33:09,770 --> 00:33:10,700
Director Zhang,

702
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,630
why don't you say a few words?

703
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:13,740
Okay.

704
00:33:15,540 --> 00:33:17,070
Regarding the use

705
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:18,830
of this 50,000 yuan in funding,

706
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,250
I have

707
00:33:21,110 --> 00:33:22,270
some new ideas.

708
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,600
I'd like to discuss with you.

709
00:33:25,350 --> 00:33:27,810
After discussing
among the leadership team

710
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:29,310
and a democratic vote

711
00:33:29,420 --> 00:33:30,400
by all staff,

712
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:33,810
the hospital has decided

713
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:36,270
to spend the funds
for renovating the shower room

714
00:33:36,270 --> 00:33:37,920
on purchasing

715
00:33:38,010 --> 00:33:39,870
menstrual belt and toilet paper,

716
00:33:40,010 --> 00:33:41,010
and distribute them

717
00:33:41,010 --> 00:33:42,180
to the country's 20 pastoral villages

718
00:33:42,180 --> 00:33:43,220
for free.

719
00:33:43,790 --> 00:33:45,010
The remaining funds

720
00:33:45,110 --> 00:33:46,050
will be used for

721
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:47,010
partial renovation

722
00:33:47,010 --> 00:33:48,270
of the shower facilities

723
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:50,000
and purchasing work supplies.

724
00:33:51,380 --> 00:33:53,360
Now, let's invite Director Zhang

725
00:33:53,390 --> 00:33:54,650
to explain to everyone

726
00:33:54,740 --> 00:33:55,660
the practical significance

727
00:33:55,660 --> 00:33:56,990
of the hygiene care plan

728
00:33:57,090 --> 00:33:58,690
for women in pastoral areas.

729
00:34:04,530 --> 00:34:05,240
This investigation report

730
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,610
on the gynecological diseases

731
00:34:06,610 --> 00:34:07,610
in pastoral areas

732
00:34:07,700 --> 00:34:10,030
was done by Yan, Zhuang,

733
00:34:10,190 --> 00:34:11,420
and Lu.

734
00:34:12,210 --> 00:34:13,110
To be honest,

735
00:34:13,420 --> 00:34:15,070
before seeing this report,

736
00:34:15,710 --> 00:34:17,030
I didn't expect

737
00:34:17,070 --> 00:34:18,929
the situation to be this serious.

738
00:34:19,460 --> 00:34:21,699
The report sampled a total

739
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:22,650
of 890 women

740
00:34:22,670 --> 00:34:23,980
aged between 18

741
00:34:24,010 --> 00:34:24,730
and 45

742
00:34:25,030 --> 00:34:26,090
in pastoral areas.

743
00:34:26,780 --> 00:34:27,440
Among them,

744
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,690
534 suffered from

745
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,260
one or more

746
00:34:31,620 --> 00:34:33,260
reproductive tract infections.

747
00:34:33,260 --> 00:34:34,469
The prevalence rate is as high as

748
00:34:34,469 --> 00:34:35,429
60 percent.

749
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:37,280
In the past,

750
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:39,230
we always attributed the cause

751
00:34:39,230 --> 00:34:40,110
to their poor hygiene habits

752
00:34:40,110 --> 00:34:41,650
and a lack of

753
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,280
physiological hygiene knowledge.

754
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:45,960
However,

755
00:34:46,050 --> 00:34:47,960
after the visits

756
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:50,110
and investigation during this period,

757
00:34:50,110 --> 00:34:51,880
the reality I saw is that,

758
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:53,730
let alone safe

759
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:55,210
and convenient sanitary pads,

760
00:34:55,210 --> 00:34:55,949
even a simple

761
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:57,620
roll of toilet paper,

762
00:34:57,650 --> 00:34:59,590
many of them can't afford

763
00:34:59,980 --> 00:35:01,310
or find anywhere to buy.

764
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,200
To this day, they are still using

765
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:04,690
wool and scrap cloth.

766
00:35:06,540 --> 00:35:07,940
Under these conditions,

767
00:35:08,050 --> 00:35:10,190
even if we educate

768
00:35:10,530 --> 00:35:11,620
all the women

769
00:35:11,650 --> 00:35:13,820
and ensure they have hygiene knowledge,

770
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:15,880
it won't solve the practical problem

771
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:18,080
or lower the incidence rate.

772
00:35:18,820 --> 00:35:21,210
Only by preventing disease
before it strikes,

773
00:35:21,210 --> 00:35:22,960
and treating it before it develops,

774
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:25,730
is it possible to change this

775
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:27,440
terrible situation.

776
00:35:28,170 --> 00:35:29,010
I believe

777
00:35:29,690 --> 00:35:32,170
this money will be well spent.

778
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:39,680
Regarding

779
00:35:39,700 --> 00:35:41,510
the funds for the shower room renovation,

780
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:44,040
the hospital will continue
to apply for them.

781
00:35:44,130 --> 00:35:46,460
The higher authorities have also given us

782
00:35:46,500 --> 00:35:48,500
sufficient attention and support.

783
00:35:49,420 --> 00:35:50,690
We'll try to start
in the second half of this year,

784
00:35:50,690 --> 00:35:51,190
no,

785
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:53,260
the second half of next year.

786
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:54,530
We also hope

787
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:55,890
everyone can overcome

788
00:35:55,980 --> 00:35:57,780
these temporary difficulties.

789
00:35:57,820 --> 00:35:58,500
Is that okay?

790
00:35:58,500 --> 00:36:00,130
Secretary Li, Director Zhang.

791
00:36:00,130 --> 00:36:00,730
Zhao,

792
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:02,290
what are you doing?

793
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:03,550
I get it now.

794
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:05,170
The hospital leadership

795
00:36:05,170 --> 00:36:06,480
isn't here to discuss this with us.

796
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:07,590
You're just here to notify us.

797
00:36:07,590 --> 00:36:08,790
Watch your attitude.

798
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:09,390
Sit down.

799
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:11,130
Don't silent him.

800
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,690
The hospital isn't a one-man show.

801
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:14,960
If anyone else has thoughts,

802
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:15,900
speak up.

803
00:36:16,460 --> 00:36:17,390
Director Zhang.

804
00:36:18,300 --> 00:36:19,710
The people in the pastoral areas
are humans,

805
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:20,710
but aren't we too?

806
00:36:21,170 --> 00:36:21,650
We all have been looking forward

807
00:36:21,650 --> 00:36:23,240
to the shower room for a long time.

808
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:24,940
Every few months you say you'll fix them.

809
00:36:24,940 --> 00:36:26,140
It's becoming a myth.

810
00:36:26,710 --> 00:36:27,380
Now the funds

811
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:28,500
has finally been approved.

812
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,700
Why did you cancel it through a meeting?

813
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:32,560
I'm not saying this

814
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:34,130
for myself.

815
00:36:35,030 --> 00:36:35,870
If we were in

816
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:37,160
any other profession,

817
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:38,030
when it’s too cold

818
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:38,820
to shower,

819
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,000
we just wouldn't.

820
00:36:41,010 --> 00:36:42,400
But we are doctors.

821
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:43,550
Maintaining personal hygiene

822
00:36:43,550 --> 00:36:44,680
is our duty.

823
00:36:45,710 --> 00:36:47,280
Sometimes when it gets busy,

824
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:49,090
we have to wash two or three times a day.

825
00:36:49,090 --> 00:36:50,110
A lot of the female colleagues

826
00:36:50,110 --> 00:36:51,840
have cried because of the cold.

827
00:36:53,650 --> 00:36:55,010
The one who left in March,

828
00:36:55,010 --> 00:36:55,670
Li Weidong.

829
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:58,080
How did he break his leg?

830
00:36:59,130 --> 00:37:00,380
Wasn't it because he took a shower

831
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:01,440
and caught a chill,

832
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:02,470
hence while he was going on rounds,

833
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:03,730
he fell off the horse?

834
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:06,190
Back then,

835
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:07,850
he didn't blame the hospital.

836
00:37:08,030 --> 00:37:08,900
Because he knew

837
00:37:09,070 --> 00:37:10,200
nobody could change

838
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:11,430
the conditions here.

839
00:37:15,190 --> 00:37:16,250
But what about now?

840
00:37:18,630 --> 00:37:19,480
I know I can't change

841
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:20,940
the hospital's decision.

842
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,820
But I just wanted to say it.

843
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,610
I feel better now that I've said it.

844
00:37:29,070 --> 00:37:30,330
I'm going back to work.

845
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:56,070
Sir.

846
00:38:03,670 --> 00:38:04,860
Actually,

847
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:05,840
when Chairman Gewang

848
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,760
organized the staff vote,

849
00:38:08,050 --> 00:38:10,030
some people did disagree.

850
00:38:10,130 --> 00:38:10,730
But in the end,

851
00:38:10,730 --> 00:38:12,660
the minority obeyed the majority.

852
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,110
I don't know

853
00:38:14,140 --> 00:38:15,870
what got into Zhao Hai just now.

854
00:38:17,550 --> 00:38:19,070
I didn't expect

855
00:38:19,090 --> 00:38:20,590
everyone to be so upset.

856
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,440
No.

857
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:24,830
Most people are still supportive.

858
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:28,570
Yanzi.

859
00:38:29,260 --> 00:38:30,320
Do you think

860
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:33,150
I made a mistake?

861
00:38:36,210 --> 00:38:37,670
So you blame me, too.

862
00:38:38,710 --> 00:38:39,400
No.

863
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,380
I just...

864
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,500
It's the first time

865
00:38:45,530 --> 00:38:46,860
I hear you reflecting.

866
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:49,460
I don't know what to say.

867
00:38:51,010 --> 00:38:52,230
When I was young,

868
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,380
we had nothing here.

869
00:38:56,210 --> 00:38:57,380
I just wanted

870
00:38:57,870 --> 00:38:59,390
to cure all the patients

871
00:39:00,070 --> 00:39:01,430
and build the hospital.

872
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:03,300
So,

873
00:39:04,220 --> 00:39:05,230
no matter how much hardship

874
00:39:05,230 --> 00:39:06,550
or suffering I went through,

875
00:39:06,550 --> 00:39:08,000
I felt it was worth it.

876
00:39:08,990 --> 00:39:10,300
I never thought about

877
00:39:11,780 --> 00:39:13,230
how the things I thought were right

878
00:39:13,230 --> 00:39:15,190
would make those around me feel.

879
00:39:18,070 --> 00:39:19,220
Times have changed.

880
00:39:21,190 --> 00:39:22,420
I became a mother,

881
00:39:23,050 --> 00:39:25,180
and took charge of the whole hospital.

882
00:39:27,190 --> 00:39:28,640
I can no longer be

883
00:39:28,670 --> 00:39:30,270
that solitary little doctor

884
00:39:30,860 --> 00:39:32,390
who only cares about herself

885
00:39:32,390 --> 00:39:33,540
and her patients.

886
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,530
As a mother and a director,

887
00:39:39,490 --> 00:39:41,220
I've been incompetent at both.

888
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:48,440
What?

889
00:39:49,460 --> 00:39:51,190
Aren't you going to comfort me?

890
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,230
Why are you

891
00:39:55,330 --> 00:39:55,860
suddenly

892
00:39:55,860 --> 00:39:57,120
so sentimental today?

893
00:39:58,610 --> 00:39:59,360
I'm tired.

894
00:40:00,420 --> 00:40:01,300
And old.

895
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:05,400
Are you going through menopause?

896
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:05,930
Get lost.

897
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:06,890
Stop joking.

898
00:40:06,970 --> 00:40:08,300
It's too early for that.

899
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:09,340
No, it's not.

900
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:10,150
You can't go against

901
00:40:10,150 --> 00:40:11,410
medical common sense.

902
00:40:29,020 --> 00:40:29,770
Did everyone understand

903
00:40:29,770 --> 00:40:31,000
what I just said?

904
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:32,320
This is important.

905
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,530
We understood.

906
00:40:33,630 --> 00:40:35,360
County Mayor Duo, you're back.

907
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:36,780
Director Zhang.

908
00:40:36,780 --> 00:40:38,910
We're borrowing your home for awhile.

909
00:40:39,500 --> 00:40:40,670
Please, sit.

910
00:40:42,870 --> 00:40:44,800
You don't recognize your own home?

911
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:45,450
I thought

912
00:40:45,470 --> 00:40:47,570
I was at the County Women's Federation.

913
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:48,920
You're actually right.

914
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,480
We are discussing

915
00:40:50,500 --> 00:40:52,130
the women's issues in our county.

916
00:40:52,130 --> 00:40:52,570
Come here.

917
00:40:52,570 --> 00:40:53,700
Sit down and listen.

918
00:40:54,110 --> 00:40:55,080
Our future work

919
00:40:55,110 --> 00:40:56,340
will need your help.

920
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:57,990
What is the problem

921
00:40:58,130 --> 00:40:59,730
with the women in our county?

922
00:41:02,790 --> 00:41:04,680
They lack gynecological knowledge.

923
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:06,600
We need to educate everyone
as soon as possible

924
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:09,130
and launch gynecological health education.

925
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,440
This is very important.

926
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:14,210
I won't join the discussion.

927
00:41:14,210 --> 00:41:15,090
You guys talk.

928
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:16,360
If you need any cooperation,

929
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,240
I'll tell Lin.

930
00:41:17,270 --> 00:41:18,270
County Mayor Duo.

931
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,130
Duojie, come back here.

932
00:41:20,900 --> 00:41:21,800
Why are you still following me

933
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:22,570
to lecture me?

934
00:41:22,570 --> 00:41:23,970
Should I be listening to this?

935
00:41:23,970 --> 00:41:25,030
Why shouldn't you?

936
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,040
Stop right there.

937
00:41:30,940 --> 00:41:32,370
Cairen was sick before.

938
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:33,450
Did you know that?

939
00:41:34,890 --> 00:41:35,870
Was it a cold?

940
00:41:36,990 --> 00:41:37,680
Do you think

941
00:41:37,710 --> 00:41:39,040
every illness is a cold?

942
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:41,120
She... she said she had a cold.

943
00:41:41,450 --> 00:41:43,080
She always has stomach aches.

944
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:44,280
Haven't you noticed?

945
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,310
Is it like me,

946
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:49,110
having a gastric ulcer?

947
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:52,680
It's caused by a gynecological issue.

948
00:41:53,810 --> 00:41:54,780
Don't you start

949
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,130
having any prejudices.

950
00:42:00,860 --> 00:42:01,490
How did she

951
00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:03,390
suddenly get this disease?

952
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,580
It's not sudden at all.

953
00:42:06,270 --> 00:42:07,730
Conditions here are limited.

954
00:42:07,730 --> 00:42:10,050
When Cairen and the others have their periods,

955
00:42:10,050 --> 00:42:11,710
let alone sanitary products,

956
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:13,260
even decent toilet paper

957
00:42:13,260 --> 00:42:14,030
is unavailable to them.

958
00:42:14,030 --> 00:42:15,780
They have to use wool for padding.

959
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:16,840
That stuff

960
00:42:16,940 --> 00:42:17,780
is rough

961
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,880
and unhygienic.

962
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:20,500
It easily causes infection.

963
00:42:20,820 --> 00:42:22,350
It's no wonder she got sick.

964
00:42:25,510 --> 00:42:26,400
The toilet paper

965
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:28,000
she brought home before

966
00:42:28,150 --> 00:42:28,920
was actually...

967
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:29,670
Yes,

968
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:31,510
you and Tashi used it all.

969
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,640
Director Zhang,

970
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:37,600
this is a big problem.

971
00:42:38,130 --> 00:42:39,360
But what can I do?

972
00:42:40,340 --> 00:42:41,920
Since it's about women,

973
00:42:42,270 --> 00:42:44,270
it's awkward for me to get involved.

974
00:42:44,420 --> 00:42:45,150
You...

975
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,560
in your daily life,

976
00:42:46,940 --> 00:42:48,420
take better care of your family.

977
00:42:48,420 --> 00:42:48,920
Okay.

978
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,680
Stop making Cairen do heavy chores

979
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:52,020
like carrying water.

980
00:42:52,470 --> 00:42:53,160
Right.

981
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,550
Carrying water.

982
00:42:56,580 --> 00:42:57,020
Okay.

983
00:43:00,340 --> 00:43:02,070
The toilet paper I left behind,

984
00:43:02,340 --> 00:43:03,900
you and Tashi aren't allowed to use it.

985
00:43:03,900 --> 00:43:04,510
Okay.

986
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:06,200
It's all for Cairen.

987
00:43:06,230 --> 00:43:06,560
Okay.

988
00:43:06,740 --> 00:43:07,670
I'll do as you say, Director Zhang.
